    <section id="id1170863950955">
      <title>Reactivity</title>
      <para id="id6527143">All the alkali metals are highly reactive and are as a consequence of the stability of the M<sup>+</sup> ion are strong reducing agents (<link target-id="id1170880242224"/>). The metals react readily with hydrogen and oxygen. </para>

      


      <equation id="eip-35"><media id="id1170884421831_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/graphics11-8316.jpg" id="id1170884421831__onlineimage" width="500" print-width="4.5in"/>
        </media>
      </equation>

      <equation id="eip-233"><media id="id6165006_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/graphics12-89bd.jpg" id="id6165006__onlineimage" width="500" print-width="4.5in"/>
        </media>
</equation><table id="id1170880242224" summary="Electrochemical reduction potential for alkali metals.">
